If you are already receiving child benefits, such as the universal child care benefit (UCCB) or the Canada child tax benefit (CCTB), or both, you do not have to apply for the Canada child benefit.

Did you know Banff National Park created a special refuge for a species at risk – the westslope cutthroat trout? 

In Alberta alone, westslope cutthroat trout occupy less than 10% of their historical range. Westslope cutthroat trout remain in only about 55 small locations in Alberta, ten of which are in Banff National Park. Parks Canada is therefore an important partner in recovery efforts for this species! Learn more: http://ow.ly/KJWbQ #WildlifeWednesday

caption_original:
The Bartholomew River, which runs through the Miramichi region of New Brunswick, has long been a favourite destination for anglers. The wild Atlantic salmon that ply its waters support recreational fisheries and are an important food source for Indigenous communities.

Environment and Climate Change Canada is partnering with the Nature Conservancy of Canada to protect the Bartholomew River and restore and enhance this important salmon habitat. Protecting the river and its adjacent forestland from future development will improve water quality and help to regulate the water temperature of the river, improving fish health. http://ow.ly/pNH8301ILpQ

If you’re looking for a summer job or you want to work while attending a post-secondary school, consider applying to the Federal Student Work Experience Program (FSWEP).

FSWEP is a great opportunity for full-time students to explore their interests, develop skills AND make some extra money. A placement through the program is also a great start for anyone considering a career in the public service.

The process is ongoing and some departments start their selection for summer 2017 as early as this August.

Learn more about FSWEP and submit your application today: http://ow.ly/7mGg301BYgW

When it comes to building bridges we tend to focus on the impacts on local residents during construction and the benefits to travelers once completed. But what about the animals? The new Champlain Bridge is being built with all critters in mind. 

During construction, fish passages will allow finned friends to navigate the jetties in the water where work is taking place. Endangered brown snakes in the vicinity of the project will be relocated to safer homes and new habitat will be created nearby to ensure the snakes can repopulate the area after the work is completed. The new bridge will feature nesting boxes for Peregrine falcons in addition to other protective measures for migratory birds. 

The small area of bird habitat affected by the construction has been well documented and new habitat and nesting sites will be created to compensate for this loss.
caption_cleaned: When it comes to building bridges we tend to focus on the impacts on local residents during construction and the benefits to travelers once completed. But what about the animals? The new Champlain Bridge is being built with all critters in mind. During construction, fish passages will allow finned friends to navigate the jetties in the water where work is taking place. Endangered brown snakes in the vicinity of the project will be relocated to safer homes and new habitat will be created nearby to ensure the snakes can repopulate the area after the work is completed. The new bridge will feature nesting boxes for Peregrine falcons in addition to other protective measures for migratory birds. The small area of bird habitat affected by the construction has been well documented and new habitat and nesting sites will be created to compensate for this loss.

#DYK that leaving the hose running when washing your car uses about 400 litres of water per car wash?

Learn more on how to best watch your water consumption: http://ow.ly/7yDX300U133 #CanadianEnvironmentWeek

#DYK a home inspection can save you money?

Like a health or dental check-up, getting an inspection before there is a problem will save you in the long run. Even if you’ve lived in your home for a number of years, having a complete inspection can give you a snapshot of your home’s condition and may identify any issues before they grow into larger problems. By catching them early you could save a lot of money.

Find a home inspector you can count on:
http://ow.ly/Lqcp3018rsF
